                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#49r" facs="053">Fol. 49r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5650Jacob">ያዕቆብ፡</persName> stands in the center; <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s ascend and descend on either side</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#83r" facs="087">Fol. 83r</locus><desc>Equestrian Saint <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>, with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> raised. Opponent with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and shield lies on the ground</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#127r" facs="131">Fol. 127r</locus><desc>Equestrian Saint <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>, with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> raised. Opponent with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and shield lies on the ground</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #7r #13r #19v #28v #35r #40v #48v #58v #66r #71r #82v #94r #96v #102r #107v #118v #126v" facs="005 011 017 024 033 039 045 053 063 070 075 087 098 101 106 112 123 131">folss. 1r, 7r, 13r, 19v, 28v, 35r, 40v, 48v, 58v, 66r, 71r, 82v, 94r, 96v, 102r, 107v, 118v, 126v, </locus> (fine #colorful harägs);
                      <locus target="#4v #27v #36r" facs="009 032 040">4v, 27v, 36r, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#129r #134v #135v #141v" facs="133 139 140 146">129r, 134v, 135v, 141v</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#141v" facs="146"> f. 141v (col. 1)</locus>: Concluding Prayer of Gate of Light [Anqäsä Bǝrhan ],
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                      ጸሎታ፡ ለማርያም፡ ወስእለታ፡ ለሕዝበ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ያድኅነነ፡ ኢመዓተ፡ ወልዳ። ጸሎታ፡ ለማርያም፡ ወስእለታ፡ ለገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ያድኅኖ፡ እመዓተ፡ ወልዳ። ጸሎታ፡ ለማርያም፡ ወስእለታ፡ ለወለተ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ያድኅና፡ እመዓተ፡ ወልዳ።
                      </foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#141v #142r #142" facs="146 147">Fols. 141v, 142r, 142</locus>: Table Prayer, “We beseech you,” Sä’alnakä, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአልናከ፡</foreign>, (MD59 634ff). (incomplete at the end)
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez"><gap reason="omitted"/>ሰአልናከ፡ መሐሪ፡ ናስተበቊዓከ፡ ዘኢትፈልእ(ጥ)፡ ወኢትከልፅ፡ ወኢትሌሊ፡ የማንከ፡ ነቅዓ፡ ሕይወት፡...</foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                      <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">
                      <locus target="#141v" facs="146"> f. 141v, col.1</locus>: Copied for Gäbrä Ḥǝywät and Wälättä Arägawi
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                        This codex has all of the marks of having been produced in the earlytwentieth
                        century government scriptorium: finely tooled leather,
                        trimmed turn-ins, fabric pasted to front and back boards, distinctive
                        harägs, the head band and tail band are two-toned, with white and
                        red strips of leather, fine and regular parchment, etc
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto) #ivv(erso) #143r #143v #144r #144v" facs="001 002 003 004 005 147 148 149">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), iiir(ecto), iiiv(erso), ivr(ecto), ivv(erso), 143r, 143v, 144r, 144v</locus> blank save for a few letters and pen trials
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#53v" facs="058">Fol. 53v</locus>: The text “half of it is here” is written the margin and enclosed in an ornate box to mark the midpoint of the psalms. The symbol is one line above the normal location
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–7
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#20r #113r" facs="024 117">folss. 20r, 113r, </locus>);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3r #24v #70r #80v #84r" facs="007 029 074 085 089">3r, 24v, 70r, 80v, 84r, </locus>, etc.);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#114r" facs="118">114r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e6">
                      <desc>
                        This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the
                        width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written
                        smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#11v #14r #16v #17v" facs="016 018 021 022">folss. 11v, 14r, 16v, 17v, </locus>).
                        Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line. In these cases, the scribe places the
                        material above the line (e.g., <locus target="#6v #108r #115v" facs="011 112 120">6v, 108r, 115v</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 153 x 100 x 53 mm, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, covered with tooled leather, with decorative linen patches visible between the turn-ins, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
